{ By Reuters   Published:  06:17, 13 February 2020   https://www.dailymail.co.uk//wires/reuters/article-7998799/Romania--Factors-watch-Feb-13.html }
BUCHAREST, Feb 13 (Reuters) - Here are news stories, press reports and events to watch which may affect Romanian financial markets on Thursday. INFLATION The National Statistics Board will release consumer price inflation data for January at 0700 GMT. The median forecast of a Reuters poll of analysts puts Romanian inflation at 3.6% year-on-year at the end of January, down from December's 4.0%. DEBT TENDER The finance ministry plans to sell 400 million lei ($91.56 million) worth of 2034 treasury bonds series RO4KELYFLVK4 at tender. It last sold the paper at an average accepted yield of 4.78% in January. CURRENT ACCOUNT DATA The central bank will release 2019 current account balance data. The external shortfall widened by 21% on the year to 9.9 billion euros ($10.79 billion) in the first 11 months of 2019. INDUSTRY Adjusted industrial output edged 0.1% down on the month in December after November's 0.2% fall, and was down 6.9% on the year, data from the National Statistics Board showed on Wednesday. CEE MARKETS The Hungarian forint hit a record low of 339.60 to the euro on Wednesday, underperforming its regional peers as investors dismissed central bank measures aimed at shoring up the currency. For other related news, double click on: --------------------------------------------------------------- Romanian equities RO-E E.Europe equities .CEE Romanian money RO-M Romanian debt RO-D Eastern Europe EEU All emerging markets EMRG Hot stocks HOT Stock markets STX Market debt news DBT Forex news FRX For real-time index quotes, double click on: Bucharest BETI Warsaw WIG20 Budapest BUX Prague PX ------------------------------------------------------- ($1 = 4.3689 lei) ($1 = 0.9173 euros) 
